001package io.cyborgcode.roa.ui.util;
002
003/**
004 * Represents a function that accepts four input arguments and produces a result.
005 *
006 * <p>This functional interface is similar to {@link java.util.function.BiFunction}, but it
007 * supports four parameters instead of two. It is primarily used for exception handling
008 * in WebElement interactions within Selenium-based test automation.
009 *
010 * <p>The first argument, {@code T}, represents the primary entity involved in the operation.
011 * The second argument, {@code U}, provides contextual information or additional parameters.
012 * The third argument, {@code V}, captures supplementary data relevant to the action.
013 * The fourth argument, {@code K}, is typically used for handling exceptions or other metadata.
014 * The return value, {@code R}, represents the computed result of the function.
015 *
016 * @author Cyborg Code Syndicate üíçüë®üíª
017 */
018@FunctionalInterface
019public interface FourFunction<T, U, V, K, R> {
020
021   /**
022    * Applies this function to the given arguments and returns a result.
023    *
024    * @param t The first input argument.
025    * @param u The second input argument.
026    * @param k The third input argument.
027    * @param v The fourth input argument.
028    * @return The function result.
029    */
030   R apply(T t, U u, K k, V v);
031}
